### Test Authentication Endpoints

### 1. Register a new user
POST https://localhost:7000/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test123!",
  "fullName": "Test User",
  "phoneNumber": "1234567890"
}

### 2. Login with the registered user
POST https://localhost:7000/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test123!"
}

### 3. Test protected endpoint (replace TOKEN with actual token from login response)
GET https://localhost:7000/api/v1/task
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Refresh token (replace REFRESH_TOKEN with actual refresh token from login response)
POST https://localhost:7000/api/v1/auth/refresh-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 5. Revoke token (replace REFRESH_TOKEN with actual refresh token)
POST https://localhost:7000/api/v1/auth/revoke-token
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}
